# Teaching workflow (Tim)

Tim's priority: **teaching runs smoothly**. Pure Canonical Core stays a separate repo.

## Three AI lanes (use the right one)

| Lane | When | Where |
|------|------|--------|
| **TIM / SETH** | Students in class; in-app chat, quizzes, study mode | `/SETH`, `/StudyAssistant` — Base44 `InvokeLLM` |
| **Classroom bridge** | Draft announcements, list courses, post to Google Classroom with AYA gate | `npm run teach:*` → `classroom-chatgpt-bridge` |
| **ChatGPT (Cursor extension)** | Lesson planning, rubrics, email drafts, Classroom announcements — you review before publish | OpenAI ChatGPT sidebar in Cursor; use `/ClassroomDraftHelper` for structured prompts, or paste into TIM |

Do not merge Classroom bridge secrets into TIM frontend. API keys live in `classroom-chatgpt-bridge/.env` only.

## Instructor pages (TIM)

| Page | Route | Workflow |
|------|-------|----------|
| **Classroom Draft** | `/ClassroomDraftHelper` | Structured fields → copy ChatGPT prompt → paste → AYA → post or copy |
| **Classroom AI** | `/ClassroomPublisher` | Freeform prompt → TIM `InvokeLLM` draft → AYA → post or copy command |

Also: `/SETH`, `/CourseGenerator`, `/AIContentGenerator`, `/InstructorFeedbackAssistant`, `/InstructorGrading`, `/LearningPathwayGenerator`, `/StudentProgressTracker`.

AI in TIM uses `@/api/integrations` → `InvokeLLM`. No direct OpenAI SDK in this repo.

## Classroom bridge (from TIM repo root)

Setup once in `CANONICAL/30_CODE/classroom-chatgpt-bridge`: copy `.env.example` → `.env`, set `OPENAI_API_KEY`, run `npm run teach:auth-google`.

**Before class:** If you ran the wizard once, the bridge starts at login automatically.

**One-time wizard (recommended on Mac):**

```bash
npm run teach:wizard
```

Walks through Google OAuth (if needed), installs a LaunchAgent, and verifies the bridge. After that, one-click post works whenever you're logged in.

**Manual session start (no LaunchAgent):**

```bash
npm run teach:start
```

**Wizard maintenance:**

```bash
npm run teach:wizard -- status
npm run teach:wizard -- uninstall
npm run teach:wizard -- restart
```

**CLI fallback:**

```bash
npm run teach:courses
npm run teach:draft -- "Weekly lab reminder for solar construction"
npm run teach:gate -- --text "Your draft here"
npm run teach:post -- --courseId ID --text "..." --dry-run
```

All Classroom posts must pass AYA policy (`config/aya-policy.json` in bridge repo). Server re-runs AYA on every post.

**Deployed TIM caveat:** Browsers may prompt for Private Network Access when a public HTTPS site calls localhost. Local dev (`npm run dev`) is fully reliable.

## Agent behavior

- Treat teaching UX bugs and broken LMS flows as **P0** during class.
- Prefer minimal diffs on SETH and instructor pages.
- When drafting content for Tim, match AYA-appropriate tone: clear, inclusive, secondary/college level unless specified.
- Route Program OS / curriculum spine work to `canonical-program-os`, not TIM.
